Simplified markdown
Version: 1.0 (main)

Usage:
mdr [-hvi] [-f file] [-t int]
    [-m char] [-r int]

-f    the name of the markup file
-t    indent for the second and subsequent
      lines of the list (number of spaces)
-m    symbol-marker of the unnumbered list
-r    value of the red line
-h    output of help with a description of the program
-v    displaying the program version
-i    flag for perfect redirection to file
